> - Read `/root/coordination/CODEBASE_CONTEXT.md` for project conventions
> - Read `/root/coordination/KNOWN_BUG_PATTERNS.md` for past incidents
> - Include in task description: "Check CODEBASE_CONTEXT.md and KNOWN_BUG_PATTERNS.md first"

**Template A — Bug Fix (Simple) — Developer Team Workflow:**
```
on the bug report:
   ┌─ Kora (Tech Lead): analyze → assign
   │
   ├─ DevOps: fix_safety.py snapshot --file <target>
   │
   ├─ Developer (Fix Agent Pro):
   │   ├─ Read CODEBASE_CONTEXT.md for project conventions
   │   ├─ Read KNOWN_BUG_PATTERNS.md for similar incidents
   │   ├── Follow FIX_AGENT_SOP.md logic thinking checklist
   │   ├─ Make targeted change
   │   ├─ python3 -m py_compile → syntax check
   │   ├─ import_scanner.py scan → import check
   │   └─ Write results to temp file
   │
   ├─ DevOps: fix_safety.py verify --file <target>
   │   ├─ PASS ✅ → continue
   │   └─ FAIL ❌ → fix_safety.py rollback → alert Kora
   │
   ├─ Auto-Verify: python3 /root/coordination/auto_verify.py
   │   ├─ PASS ✅ → continue
   │   └─ FAIL ❌ → auto rollback + alert written
   │
   ├─ QA (Verify Agent Flash):
   │   ├─ import_scanner.py scan --all-handlers (pattern scan)
   │   ├─ integration_tester.py test (full health check)
   │   ├─ flow_analyzer.py --report (check state machine integrity)
   │   ├─ enhanced_validator.py --patterns (regression check)
   │   ├─ journalctl check (zero new errors)
   │   └─ ALL PASS ✅ → proceed
   │      FAIL ❌ → rollback → alert Kora
   │
   ├─ Linter: import_scanner.py scan --modified (final pass)
   │
   │
   ├─ 📝 Docs:
   │   ├─ python3 /root/coordination/auto_doc_updater.py --summary "<fix>"
   │   └─ Append to /home/node/.openclaw/workspace/project-state/psvibe-sales-bot.md
   │
   └─ Kora (Tech Lead): summarize → report to Boss ✅
```

